  <body>
    <segment id="1">
Actually, no one is missing... </segment>
    <segment id="11" parent="2" relname="concession">

Justice Minister Schelter has so far been spared from spectacular prison breaks.</segment>
    <segment id="2" parent="24" relname="span">  

However, the justice chronicle now records an incident of a special kind for his term in office.</segment>
    <segment id="3" parent="25" relname="span"> 

The prison in Spremberg released a prisoner on Tuesday who was not even due for release.</segment>
    <segment id="4" parent="3" relname="elaboration">  

Simply due to a case of mistaken identity, the convicted thief was able to pass through the prison gate.</segment>
    <segment id="5" parent="26" relname="sequence">  

Since then, he has disappeared.</segment>
    <segment id="6" parent="12" relname="concession">  

The Justice Ministry was quick to point out yesterday that he is not dangerous,</segment>
    <segment id="12" parent="27" relname="span"> 

but - of course - he also does not yet belong to freedom.</segment>
    <segment id="7" parent="23" relname="span"> 

The Minister of course has to ask himself what is going on in Spremberg.</segment>
    <segment id="8" parent="20" relname="span">  

Someone is receiving dismissal papers ,</segment>
    <segment id="13" parent="8" relname="cause"> 

just because they happen to have the same last name as a fellow prisoner.</segment>
    <segment id="9" parent="14" relname="condition"> 

And if the wife of the person who was actually supposed to be dismissed had not asked where her husband was,</segment>
    <segment id="14" parent="19" relname="span"> 

the wrong person leaving may not have been noticed yet.</segment>
    <segment id="10" parent="18" relname="joint">  

 In Spremberg, the guards apparently operate on the simple calculation:</segment>
    <segment id="15" parent="17" relname="span"> 

the main thing is that the total number is correct,</segment>
    <segment id="16" parent="15" relname="circumstance"> 

when they lock up in the evening.</segment>
